resolution_notes:
The score remains unchanged following the review. The agent did not use the required script when calling the billing contact or when leaving a message with another party, as outlined in the KB page Call Script: Invoice Generated (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/call-script-invoice-generated
).

Additionally, the agent did not attempt to contact the Google contact, nor did she document why the Google contact was not called, as required by the KB page How to Document Methods for Making Contact (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-document-methods-for-making-contact
).

As a result, required call and documentation processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following the review. The agent did not read the required script for the scenario “The customer DOES know how updates to the network are handled and IS willing to try and update the network” after learning that the customer could have their IT team complete the update per the KB page Network Requirements – An update to the network is needed – Initial Conversation (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-tech-support/page/network-requirements-an-update-to-the-network-is-needed-initial-conversation
).

Reading this script would have provided the customer an opportunity to confirm when the network requirements would be updated, allowing the agent to follow up the next day to ensure the system was up and running. As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following review. The agent did not follow the ticket callback No Contact Follow-Up Cadences KB page (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/general-support-instructions/page/no-contact-follow-up-cadences
), which requires three follow-up calls and emails on three consecutive business days. The agent completed follow-up phone calls only and did not complete the required email follow-ups.

As a result, required call and ticket-handling processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following review. The agent did not leave a complete voicemail and did not place a return call to 805-657-8400 after the call was unexpectedly disconnected, as required by KB page Requirements Following an Unexpected Disconnection (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/phone-etiquette-tickets-and-tasks/page/requirements-following-an-unexpected-disconnection
).
As a result, required call-handling processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following review. Rather than assisting the customer, the agent checked who was assigned to the ticket, confirmed availability, and transferred the caller directly to Amanda. This action is not compliant with KB page Policy – Handling Support Inquiries as a Team (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/operations-department-policies/page/policy-handling-support-inquiries-as-a-team
), which states that calls should only be transferred when the customer requires support outside of the CSR’s assigned job duties.

Additionally, the agent did not follow the requirements outlined in KB page Requirements for Placing a Customer on Hold (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/phone-etiquette-tickets-and-tasks/page/requirements-for-placing-a-customer-on-hold
). The agent did not ask the customer for permission to place them on hold, nor did she inform the customer of the expected hold duration.

As a result, required call-handling processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following review. The agent did not Google the site name and address as required by the KB page Methods for Making Contact (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/methods-for-making-contact
).

Additionally, full contact methods and documentation were not completed. The notes do not indicate why the site contact and Google contact were not called, nor do they include the business hours, as required by the KB page How to Document Methods for Making Contact (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-document-methods-for-making-contact
).

As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.

The score remains unchanged following the review. The agent did not use the required scripting or follow the steps outlined in the KB article How to Process a Change of Ownership (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-process-a-change-of-ownership
).

Additionally, the agent did not follow the required scripting to send an exit survey per the KB article How to Send an Exit Survey (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-send-an-exit-survey
). The agent also did not utilize positive scripting as required by the KB article Positive Scripting – Words and Phrases (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/phone-etiquette-tickets-and-tasks/page/positive-scripting-words-and-phrases
).
As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.
